    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you said \"extreme\" nationalism leads to conflict... isn't that a bit of a way to brush off the valid points people make? like, isn't having a sense of national pride and putting your own country's interests first just common sense for stability? it feels like there's a bias in calling it \"extreme\" just because it's not globalist.",
