      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The point where nationalism becomes an objective net negative is when it translates into hostility toward others or the erosion of universal human rights. When a nation's self-interest requires the systematic oppression or exclusion of specific groups, it crosses the line into dangerous ideology. Therefore, while cultural preservation is valid, nationalism becomes definitively negative when it prioritizes the in-group at the expense of humanity.",
      "source": "target",
